title: FIELD HOCKEY
text:
FIELD HOCKEY By Journal Inquirer Staff Journal Inquirer | 0 comments 
CONARD 1, SOUTH WINDSOR 0. In South Windsor, Charlotte Leyland scored on a corner with no time left in the first half to lift Conard to the CCC interdivisional win. 
Avery Sherrill made save in the first half, and Laura Keck stopped six shots in the second half for the Chieftains (8-1-0). Mackenzie Elliot didnâ€™t make a save in the first half while Sarah Gallagher made three stops in the final 30 minutes for the Bobcats (7-2-0-1), who have dropped back-to-back 1-0 games. Bridget Kelly, Gabby Inkel, and Kalee Mabey were standouts.
